   357вҶ’### 2.2.5 Usage Patterns
   358вҶ’
   359вҶ’**Pattern 1: React Component with Selector**
   360вҶ’
   361вҶ’```typescript
   362вҶ’// Components that need reactive state updates
   363вҶ’import { useCanvasSelector, canvasActions, canvasStore } from '../state';
   364вҶ’
   365вҶ’function ZoomControls() {
   366вҶ’  // Reactive - component re-renders when zoom changes
   367вҶ’  const zoom = useCanvasSelector(s => s.viewport.camera.zoom);
   368вҶ’
   369вҶ’  const handleZoomIn = () => {
   370вҶ’    canvasStore.dispatch(canvasActions.viewport.setZoom(zoom * 1.2));
   371вҶ’  };
   372вҶ’
   373вҶ’  const handleZoomOut = () => {
   374вҶ’    canvasStore.dispatch(canvasActions.viewport.setZoom(zoom / 1.2));
   375вҶ’  };
   376вҶ’
   377вҶ’  return (
   378вҶ’    <div>
   379вҶ’      <button onClick={handleZoomOut}>-</button>
   380вҶ’      <span>{Math.round(zoom * 100)}%</span>
   381вҶ’      <button onClick={handleZoomIn}>+</button>
   382вҶ’    </div>
   383вҶ’  );
   384вҶ’}
   385вҶ’```
   386вҶ’
   387вҶ’**Pattern 2: Animation Loop (NO React Hooks)**
   388вҶ’
   389вҶ’```typescript
   390вҶ’// Animation loops MUST use store.getState() directly
   391вҶ’// NEVER use React hooks in animation loops (stale closures!)
   392вҶ’import { useFrame } from '@react-three/fiber';
   393вҶ’import { canvasStore, canvasActions } from '../state';
   394вҶ’
   395вҶ’function CameraAnimator() {
   396вҶ’  useFrame(() => {
   397вҶ’    // CORRECT: Get fresh state every frame
   398вҶ’    const state = canvasStore.getState();
   399вҶ’    const { animation, camera } = state.viewport;
   400вҶ’
   401вҶ’    if (!animation.isAnimating) return;
   402вҶ’
   403вҶ’    const elapsed = Date.now() - animation.startTime;
   404вҶ’    const progress = Math.min(elapsed / animation.duration, 1);
   405вҶ’    const eased = easeOutCubic(progress);
   406вҶ’
   407вҶ’    const newCamera = {
   408вҶ’      x: lerp(animation.startX, animation.targetX, eased),
   409вҶ’      y: lerp(animation.startY, animation.targetY, eased),
   410вҶ’      zoom: lerp(animation.startZoom, animation.targetZoom, eased),
   411вҶ’    };
   412вҶ’
   413вҶ’    canvasStore.dispatch(canvasActions.viewport.updateAnimation({
   414вҶ’      camera: newCamera
   415вҶ’    }));
   416вҶ’
   417вҶ’    if (progress >= 1) {
   418вҶ’      canvasStore.dispatch(canvasActions.viewport.stopAnimation());
   419вҶ’    }
   420вҶ’  });
   421вҶ’
   422вҶ’  return null;
   423вҶ’}
   424вҶ’
   425вҶ’function lerp(a: number, b: number, t: number): number {
   426вҶ’  return a + (b - a) * t;
   427вҶ’}
   428вҶ’
   429вҶ’function easeOutCubic(t: number): number {
   430вҶ’  return 1 - Math.pow(1 - t, 3);
   431вҶ’}
   432вҶ’```
   433вҶ’
   434вҶ’**Pattern 3: Event Handler with Direct Store Access**
   435вҶ’
   436вҶ’```typescript
   437вҶ’// Event handlers that need immediate state
   438вҶ’const handleWheel = useCallback((event: WheelEvent) => {
   439вҶ’  event.preventDefault();
   440вҶ’
   441вҶ’  // Get current state synchronously
   442вҶ’  const state = canvasStore.getState();
   443вҶ’  const { camera } = state.viewport;
   444вҶ’
   445вҶ’  // Calculate new zoom
   446вҶ’  const zoomDelta = -event.deltaY * ZOOM_SENSITIVITY;
   447вҶ’  const newZoom = clamp(camera.zoom * (1 + zoomDelta), MIN_ZOOM, MAX_ZOOM);
   448вҶ’
   449вҶ’  // Dispatch update
   450вҶ’  canvasStore.dispatch(canvasActions.viewport.setCamera({
   451вҶ’    x: camera.x,
   452вҶ’    y: camera.y,
   453вҶ’    zoom: newZoom,
   454вҶ’  }));
   455вҶ’}, []);
   456вҶ’```
   457вҶ’
   458вҶ’### 2.2.6 metadata: false Explained
   459вҶ’
   460вҶ’**Why this option is critical for 60fps:**
   461вҶ’
   462вҶ’When `metadata: true` (default), every dispatch creates:
   463вҶ’```typescript
   464вҶ’{
   465вҶ’  changes: previousChanges + 1,
   466вҶ’  updatedAt: Date.now(),
   467вҶ’  updatedByActionType: action.type,
   468вҶ’  sessionID: '...',
   469вҶ’  userID: '...',
   470вҶ’}
   471вҶ’```
   472вҶ’
   473вҶ’At 60fps with continuous updates:
   474вҶ’- 60 new objects allocated per second
   475вҶ’- Increases GC pressure
   476вҶ’- Mobile devices especially sensitive
   477вҶ’- Can cause frame drops during GC pause
   478вҶ’
   479вҶ’With `metadata: false`:
   480вҶ’- No per-dispatch allocations
   481вҶ’- State updates are direct Immer mutations
   482вҶ’- GC pressure eliminated for state updates
   483вҶ’
