# PART II: TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE

> **MMS V1.0 GENESIS Specification**
> **Document Type:** Architecture Specification
> **Version:** 1.0.0
> **Last Updated:** 2026-01-06

---

## 2.1 System Overview

### 2.1.1 Architecture Diagram

```
+==============================================================================+
|                          MMS V1.0 GENESIS ARCHITECTURE                        |
+==============================================================================+

+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                              REACT APPLICATION                                |
|                         (Vite 5.x + React 18.3.1)                            |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                                                                               |
|  +------------------+  +---------------------+  +------------------------+   |
|  |                  |  |                     |  |                        |   |
|  |    App.tsx       |  |   canvasStore       |  |   RBushSpatialIndex    |   |
|  |    (Layout)      |<-|   (@zazcart/tools)  |<-|   (O(log n) queries)   |   |
|  |                  |  |                     |  |                        |   |
|  | +------+ +-----+ |  | +-----------------+ |  | +--------------------+ |   |
|  | |Sidebar| |Time | |  | | viewport slice | |  | | tree: RBush<Task>  | |   |
|  | |      | |line | |  | | interaction    | |  | | itemsById: Map     | |   |
|  | +------+ +-----+ |  | +-----------------+ |  | +--------------------+ |   |
|  +------------------+  +---------------------+  +------------------------+   |
|           |                      |                         |                  |
|           v                      v                         v                  |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                         LOD DECISION LAYER                                    |
|    +----------------+    +----------------+    +----------------+             |
|    |  zoom < 0.5    |    | 0.5 <= z < 2.0 |    |   zoom >= 2.0  |             |
|    |     MACRO      |    |      MESO      |    |     MICRO      |             |
|    +-------+--------+    +-------+--------+    +-------+--------+             |
|            |                     |                     |                      |
+------------|---------------------|---------------------|----------------------+
             v                     v                     v
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                          RENDERING LAYERS                                     |
|                                                                               |
|  +------------------+  +---------------------+  +------------------------+   |
|  |   MacroLayer     |  |    MesoLayer        |  |    MicroLayer          |   |
|  |                  |  |                     |  |                        |   |
|  | InstancedMesh    |  |  InstancedMesh      |  |  InstancedMesh         |   |
|  | (heatmap cells)  |  |  (task blocks)      |  |  + HTML labels         |   |
|  |                  |  |                     |  |  + Line2 curves        |   |
|  | Cells: 600       |  |  Pre-alloc: 100k    |  |  Labels: max 50        |   |
|  | (50 trains x 12) |  |  Visible: ~10k      |  |  (virtual scroll)      |   |
|  +------------------+  +---------------------+  +------------------------+   |
|                                                                               |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                 REACT THREE FIBER 8.x + THREE.JS 0.170.x                     |
|                         OrthographicCamera                                    |
|                    X = Time (days) | Y = Train Index                         |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
```

### 2.1.2 Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology | Version | Purpose |
|-------|------------|---------|---------|
| **Build Tool** | Vite | 5.x | Fast HMR, ESM-first |
| **UI Framework** | React | 18.3.1 | Required for BlueprintJS 6 |
| **UI Components** | BlueprintJS | 6.1.0 | Enterprise UI components |
| **3D Renderer** | React Three Fiber | 8.17.10 | Declarative Three.js |
| **3D Helpers** | drei | 9.114.3 | R3F ecosystem |
| **3D Engine** | Three.js | 0.170.0 | WebGL rendering |
| **State** | @zazcart/tools | 0.1.0 | Slice-based state machine |
| **Spatial Index** | RBush | 4.0.1 | R-tree for O(log n) queries |
| **Immutability** | Immer | 10.2.0 | Reducer state updates |

### 2.1.3 Magna Rules Reminder

These rules are INVIOLABLE for V1.0:

| Rule | Constraint | Rationale |
|------|------------|-----------|
| **MAGNA-001** | React 18.3.1 (NOT 19) | BlueprintJS 6 requires React 18 |
| **MAGNA-002** | R3F 8.x + drei 9.x | Pairs with React 18 |
| **MAGNA-003** | 60fps minimum | Demo success criterion |
| **MAGNA-004** | Desktop-first | Mobile is V1.1 |
| **MAGNA-005** | Mock data only | No real mileage integration |
| **MAGNA-006** | @zazcart/tools for state | Avoid useState stale closures |
| **MAGNA-007** | RBush for all queries | O(log n) is mandatory |

---

## 2.2 State Management

### 2.2.1 Library Overview

**Package:** `@zazcart/tools` (located at `packages/toolkit`)

The library provides a slice-based state machine pattern (NOT FSM/XState style) with:
- Immer-powered immutable updates
- React 18 `useSyncExternalStore` integration
- Zero-allocation option for 60fps updates

**Critical Note:** `@zazcart/tools` and `@belt/tools` are the SAME library (same GitHub repo, different npm names). No API migration required.

### 2.2.2 createMachine Pattern

The central state machine combines all slices:

```typescript
// File: apps/canvas/src/state/canvas-machine.ts
import { createMachine } from '@zazcart/tools';
import { viewportSlice } from './viewport';
import { interactionSlice } from './interaction';

export const canvasMachine = createMachine({
  // Unique machine identifier
  id: 'canvas',

  // State slices to combine
  slices: {
    viewport: viewportSlice,
    interaction: interactionSlice,
  },

  // Global context (shared across slices)
  context: {
    userID: null,  // Canvas is public/anonymous
  },

  // CRITICAL: Disable metadata tracking for 60fps
  // Prevents per-dispatch object allocations that trigger GC
  metadata: false,
});

// Typed React hooks
export const useCanvas = canvasMachine.useMachine;
export const useCanvasSelector = canvasMachine.useSelector;

// Action creators (organized by slice)
export const canvasActions = canvasMachine.actions;

// Direct store access (for animation loops - NO React re-renders)
export const canvasStore = {
  getState: canvasMachine.getState,
  dispatch: canvasMachine.dispatch,
  subscribe: canvasMachine.subscribe,
};
```

### 2.2.3 createSyncSlice Pattern

Each state domain is a separate slice:

```typescript
// File: apps/canvas/src/state/viewport.ts
import { createSyncSlice } from '@zazcart/tools';

// Types
export interface CameraPosition {
  x: number;
  y: number;
  zoom: number;
}

export interface MomentumState {
  velocityX: number;
  velocityY: number;
  isActive: boolean;
}

export interface AnimationState {
  isAnimating: boolean;
  startTime: number;
  duration: number;
  startX: number;
  startY: number;
  startZoom: number;
  targetX: number;
  targetY: number;
  targetZoom: number;
}

export interface ViewportSliceState {
  camera: CameraPosition;
  canvasSize: { width: number; height: number };
  isInitialized: boolean;
  momentum: MomentumState;
  animation: AnimationState;
  isPanning: boolean;
  panStart: CameraPosition;
  cameraPosAtPanStart: CameraPosition;
}

// Initial state
const initialState: ViewportSliceState = {
  camera: { x: 0, y: 0, zoom: 1 },
  canvasSize: { width: 0, height: 0 },
  isInitialized: false,
  momentum: { velocityX: 0, velocityY: 0, isActive: false },
  animation: {
    isAnimating: false,
    startTime: 0,
    duration: 250,
    startX: 0, startY: 0, startZoom: 1,
    targetX: 0, targetY: 0, targetZoom: 1,
  },
  isPanning: false,
  panStart: { x: 0, y: 0, zoom: 1 },
  cameraPosAtPanStart: { x: 0, y: 0, zoom: 1 },
};

// Slice definition
export const viewportSlice = createSyncSlice({
  id: 'viewport',
  initial: initialState,

  // Cache strategy (session = resets on page refresh)
  cache: { policy: 'session' },

  // Reducers (Immer draft - "mutable" syntax internally immutable)
  reducers: {
    setCamera(state, payload: CameraPosition) {
      state.camera = payload;
    },

    setZoom(state, payload: number) {
      state.camera.zoom = payload;
    },

    setCanvasSize(state, payload: { width: number; height: number }) {
      state.canvasSize = payload;
      state.isInitialized = true;
    },

    startPan(state, payload: { x: number; y: number }) {
      state.isPanning = true;
      state.panStart = { x: payload.x, y: payload.y, zoom: state.camera.zoom };
      state.cameraPosAtPanStart = { ...state.camera };
    },

    endPan(state) {
      state.isPanning = false;
    },

    startMomentum(state, payload: { velocityX: number; velocityY: number }) {
      state.momentum = {
        velocityX: payload.velocityX,
        velocityY: payload.velocityY,
        isActive: true,
      };
    },

    updateMomentum(state, payload: {
      velocityX: number;
      velocityY: number;
      camera: CameraPosition
    }) {
      state.momentum.velocityX = payload.velocityX;
      state.momentum.velocityY = payload.velocityY;
      state.camera = payload.camera;
    },

    stopMomentum(state) {
      state.momentum.isActive = false;
      state.momentum.velocityX = 0;
      state.momentum.velocityY = 0;
    },

    startAnimation(state, payload: {
      targetX: number;
      targetY: number;
      targetZoom: number;
      duration?: number;
    }) {
      state.animation = {
        isAnimating: true,
        startTime: Date.now(),
        duration: payload.duration ?? 250,
        startX: state.camera.x,
        startY: state.camera.y,
        startZoom: state.camera.zoom,
        targetX: payload.targetX,
        targetY: payload.targetY,
        targetZoom: payload.targetZoom,
      };
    },

    updateAnimation(state, payload: { camera: CameraPosition }) {
      state.camera = payload.camera;
    },

    stopAnimation(state) {
      state.animation.isAnimating = false;
    },

    // Reset to default
    reset() {
      return initialState;
    },
  },
});
```

### 2.2.4 Interaction Slice

```typescript
// File: apps/canvas/src/state/interaction.ts
import { createSyncSlice } from '@zazcart/tools';

export interface InteractionSliceState {
  hoveredTaskId: string | null;
  selectedTaskId: string | null;
  focusedTaskId: string | null;
  mousePosition: { x: number; y: number } | null;
}

const initialState: InteractionSliceState = {
  hoveredTaskId: null,
  selectedTaskId: null,
  focusedTaskId: null,
  mousePosition: null,
};

export const interactionSlice = createSyncSlice({
  id: 'interaction',
  initial: initialState,
  cache: { policy: 'session' },

  reducers: {
    setHoveredTask(state, payload: string | null) {
      state.hoveredTaskId = payload;
    },

    setSelectedTask(state, payload: string | null) {
      state.selectedTaskId = payload;
    },

    setFocusedTask(state, payload: string | null) {
      state.focusedTaskId = payload;
    },

    setMousePosition(state, payload: { x: number; y: number } | null) {
      state.mousePosition = payload;
    },

    clearSelection(state) {
      state.selectedTaskId = null;
      state.focusedTaskId = null;
    },
  },
});
```

### 2.2.5 Usage Patterns

**Pattern 1: React Component with Selector**

```typescript
// Components that need reactive state updates
import { useCanvasSelector, canvasActions, canvasStore } from '../state';

function ZoomControls() {
  // Reactive - component re-renders when zoom changes
  const zoom = useCanvasSelector(s => s.viewport.camera.zoom);

  const handleZoomIn = () => {
    canvasStore.dispatch(canvasActions.viewport.setZoom(zoom * 1.2));
  };

  const handleZoomOut = () => {
    canvasStore.dispatch(canvasActions.viewport.setZoom(zoom / 1.2));
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <button onClick={handleZoomOut}>-</button>
      <span>{Math.round(zoom * 100)}%</span>
      <button onClick={handleZoomIn}>+</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

**Pattern 2: Animation Loop (NO React Hooks)**

```typescript
// Animation loops MUST use store.getState() directly
// NEVER use React hooks in animation loops (stale closures!)
import { useFrame } from '@react-three/fiber';
import { canvasStore, canvasActions } from '../state';

function CameraAnimator() {
  useFrame(() => {
    // CORRECT: Get fresh state every frame
    const state = canvasStore.getState();
    const { animation, camera } = state.viewport;

    if (!animation.isAnimating) return;

    const elapsed = Date.now() - animation.startTime;
    const progress = Math.min(elapsed / animation.duration, 1);
    const eased = easeOutCubic(progress);

    const newCamera = {
      x: lerp(animation.startX, animation.targetX, eased),
      y: lerp(animation.startY, animation.targetY, eased),
      zoom: lerp(animation.startZoom, animation.targetZoom, eased),
    };

    canvasStore.dispatch(canvasActions.viewport.updateAnimation({
      camera: newCamera
    }));

    if (progress >= 1) {
      canvasStore.dispatch(canvasActions.viewport.stopAnimation());
    }
  });

  return null;
}

function lerp(a: number, b: number, t: number): number {
  return a + (b - a) * t;
}

function easeOutCubic(t: number): number {
  return 1 - Math.pow(1 - t, 3);
}
```

**Pattern 3: Event Handler with Direct Store Access**

```typescript
// Event handlers that need immediate state
const handleWheel = useCallback((event: WheelEvent) => {
  event.preventDefault();

  // Get current state synchronously
  const state = canvasStore.getState();
  const { camera } = state.viewport;

  // Calculate new zoom
  const zoomDelta = -event.deltaY * ZOOM_SENSITIVITY;
  const newZoom = clamp(camera.zoom * (1 + zoomDelta), MIN_ZOOM, MAX_ZOOM);

  // Dispatch update
  canvasStore.dispatch(canvasActions.viewport.setCamera({
    x: camera.x,
    y: camera.y,
    zoom: newZoom,
  }));
}, []);
```

### 2.2.6 metadata: false Explained

**Why this option is critical for 60fps:**

When `metadata: true` (default), every dispatch creates:
```typescript
{
  changes: previousChanges + 1,
  updatedAt: Date.now(),
  updatedByActionType: action.type,
  sessionID: '...',
  userID: '...',
}
```

At 60fps with continuous updates:
- 60 new objects allocated per second
- Increases GC pressure
- Mobile devices especially sensitive
- Can cause frame drops during GC pause

With `metadata: false`:
- No per-dispatch allocations
- State updates are direct Immer mutations
- GC pressure eliminated for state updates

---

## 2.3 Canvas Architecture

### 2.3.1 React Three Fiber Integration

**Version Pairing (Critical):**

| React Version | R3F Version | drei Version | Notes |
|---------------|-------------|--------------|-------|
| **React 18** | **R3F 8.x** | **drei 9.x** | **MMS V1.0** |
| React 19 | R3F 9.x | drei 10.x | Future (breaking changes) |

**Why React 18:**
- BlueprintJS 6 requires React 18
- R3F 8.x is stable and well-tested
- No benefit to upgrading for demo

### 2.3.2 OrthographicCamera Configuration

```typescript
// File: apps/canvas/src/canvas/InfiniteCanvas.tsx

// Camera configuration constants
const CAMERA_NEAR = -1000;
const CAMERA_FAR = 1000;
const INITIAL_ZOOM = 1;
const MIN_ZOOM = 0.1;
const MAX_ZOOM = 5;

// The canvas uses R3F's orthographic camera for 2D visualization
<Canvas
  orthographic
  camera={{
    position: [0, 0, 100],  // Z doesn't affect 2D view
    zoom: INITIAL_ZOOM,
    near: CAMERA_NEAR,
    far: CAMERA_FAR,
  }}
  gl={{
    antialias: true,
    alpha: false,  // Opaque background for performance
    powerPreference: 'high-performance',
  }}
  style={{ width: '100%', height: '100%' }}
>
  <CameraController />
  <LODLayers />
</Canvas>
```

### 2.3.3 Coordinate System

```
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                            CANVAS COORDINATE SYSTEM                           |
+------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

                                    +X (Time - Days)
                                    |
                                    |
        (-) Past                    |                    (+) Future
   <--------------------------------+--------------------------------->
                                    |
                   Day 0 = meta.startDate (2024-01-01)


+Y (Trains - negative because canvas Y grows down)
|
|  Train 0:  y = 0
|  Train 1:  y = -24 (PX_PER_TRAIN)
|  Train 2:  y = -48
|  ...
|  Train 49: y = -1176
v

Constants:
  PX_PER_DAY = 10      // 1 day = 10 pixels (X scale)
  PX_PER_TRAIN = 24    // 1 train row = 24 pixels (Y scale)

Conversion Functions:
  worldX = (date - startDate) / DAY_MS * PX_PER_DAY
  worldY = -trainIndex * PX_PER_TRAIN

Viewport:
  Camera position (x, y) is CENTER of visible area
  Visible width = canvasWidth / zoom
  Visible height = canvasHeight / zoom
```

### 2.3.4 CameraController Component

```typescript
// Camera position is managed via state, synced to Three.js camera
function CameraController() {
  const camera = useThree((state) => state.camera);
  const { camera: cameraState } = useCanvasSelector(s => s.viewport);

  // Sync state to Three.js camera
  useFrame(() => {
    if (camera instanceof OrthographicCamera) {
      camera.position.x = cameraState.x;
      camera.position.y = cameraState.y;
      camera.zoom = cameraState.zoom;
      camera.updateProjectionMatrix();
    }
  });

  return null;
}
