### 2.6.2 Type Flow: Persistent -> Render

```typescript
// 1. Generator creates PERSISTENT data (serializable)
interface Task {
  id: string;
  trainId: string;
  startDate: string;      // ISO 8601: "2024-03-15"
  endDate: string;
  type: TaskType;
  hasConflict: boolean;
}

// 2. Transform to RENDER data (calculated)
interface TaskRender {
  id: string;
  trainIndex: number;     // Calculated from trainId
  startDay: number;       // Days since meta.startDate
  duration: number;       // Days
  color: TaskColor;       // Derived from type
  hasConflict: boolean;
  type: TaskType;
}

// 3. Transform function
function prepareRenderData(data: GeneratedData): TaskRender[] {
  const trainIndexMap = new Map(
    data.trains.map((t, i) => [t.id, i])
  );
  const startDate = new Date(data.meta.startDate);

  return data.tasks.map(task => ({
    id: task.id,
    trainIndex: trainIndexMap.get(task.trainId)!,
    startDay: daysBetween(startDate, new Date(task.startDate)),
    duration: daysBetween(new Date(task.startDate), new Date(task.endDate)),
    color: TYPE_TO_COLOR[task.type],
    hasConflict: task.hasConflict,
    type: task.type,
  }));
}
```

### 2.6.3 Viewport Culling Flow

```
+-------------------------------------------------------------------+
|                      VIEWPORT CULLING FLOW                         |
+-------------------------------------------------------------------+

1. User pans/zooms canvas
        |
        v
2. Camera position updates in state
        |
        v
3. Calculate viewport bounds in world coordinates:

   viewportBounds = {
     minX: camera.x - (canvasWidth / 2) / zoom,
     maxX: camera.x + (canvasWidth / 2) / zoom,
     minY: camera.y - (canvasHeight / 2) / zoom,
     maxY: camera.y + (canvasHeight / 2) / zoom,
   }
        |
        v
4. Query RBush spatial index (O(log n + k)):

   visibleTaskIds = spatialIndex.queryViewport(viewportBounds)
        |
        v
5. Map IDs to TaskRender objects:

   visibleTasks = visibleTaskIds.map(id => taskMap.get(id))
        |
        v
6. Update InstancedMesh with visible tasks:

   mesh.count = visibleTasks.length
   for (task, i) of visibleTasks:
     mesh.setMatrixAt(i, computeMatrix(task))
     mesh.setColorAt(i, computeColor(task))
